Phase separation plays important roles in various cellular processes including:

(1) Organization of the nucleus and other organelles;
(2) Regulation of gene expression;
(3) Formation of pathological aggregates (e.g., amyloid fibrils);
(4) Cellular signaling and response to stress;

The study of phase separation has led to a deeper understanding of the complexity and dynamics of cellular organization and function.assistant

